Free vaccinations for children born in August
Beginning in January, children born on or after August 2 of last year will be able to receive the pneumococcal vaccine free of charge.
The condition is that you have not received a dose of the vaccine before.
Those who started the vaccine last year or earlier have to cover other doses of the vaccine as well.
The first dose of the vaccine must be received between the third and fifth month of age of a child.
Last year, a quarter of families voluntarily allowed their children to be vaccinated against pneumococci.
The parents, however, paid for a dose of 1600 crowns and more.
To vaccinate younger children, four doses are needed.
Experts generally estimate that insurance companies will spend 300 to 450,000 crowns annually on vaccines.
Clutch will save on treatment, which is needed for unvaccinated children.
So far the state has spent on all vaccination of children about 500,000 annually.
Covered vaccination was initiated by the so-called Janota package.
Pneumococcus is the cause of otitis media, but also of serious infections including meningitis and sepsis.
Pneumococcal infections in our country each year die according to research in hospitals 28 children not older than 10 years of age.
In addition to the Czech Republic, pneumococcal vaccine coverage in children was introduced in approximately 40 countries.
Will the vaccine be mandatory?
At the same time, however, there are opinions that this vaccine may be mandatory in the future.
From January it must be covered by insurance and voluntary companies.
