A percentage that does not oblige you to launch a public takeover bid (opa) for all securities.
In particular, Nueva Rumasa offers 1.5025 euros per share that would be disbursed in 10 years and that would be repaid with an interest for said deferral of 1% annually
Sos shares closed at 1.85 euros yesterday; therefore, Nueva Rumasa’s offer values the company 18% below the market.
According to Nueva Rumasa, the price of 1.50 euros reflects the real valuation of Sos.
The offer is conditional on the appointment of eight of the 15 councillors.
The Jerez group gives shareholders a period of 15 days to communicate their interest in selling securities.
The CNMV said it had not been informed of the offer, despite the Ruiz Mateos company claiming that it had contacted the regulator.
If carried out, the disbursement would reach 611.7 million when the capitalization of Sos is 254.27 million.
Meanwhile, Sos continues to restructure its management.
In an attempt to stay away from possible purchase offers and the judicial fluctuations of its former managers, the brothers Jes<0xC3><0xBA>s and Jaime Salazar, it announced the election of Mar<0xC3><0xAD>a Luisa Jord<0xC3><0xA1> as director of internal audit.
A decision that makes her the first woman to hold a high position in the food company.
This is a newly created position that will depend directly on the group president.
And it is not without controversy, as the company remains immersed in the legal battle for the alleged diversion of more than 230 million from Sos to Salazar societies.
In fact, it cannot be ruled out that over the next few months Sos will reveal new diversions of funds
Regarding the credit to the Salazars, yesterday the former councilors Ildefonso Ortega and <0xC3><0x81>ngel Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez Noriega (representatives of CCM and Unicaja) declared in the National Court that they approved the diversion of 212 million without knowing their fate.
CNMV authorizes the exclusion of Paternina Opa presented by Inversora Mer
The National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) yesterday authorized the exclusion opa presented by Inversora Mer on Federico Paternina last October 9.
The supervisory body has explained that it authorizes this operation on the understanding that its terms comply with the current rules and consider "sufficient" the content of the explanatory brochure presented after the changes introduced last December 2.
The CNMV has specified that the offer is directed to the acquisition of 550.008 shares of Federico Paternina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, representing 8.95% of its share capital, which is composed of 6,142,786 shares admitted to trading on the Madrid and Bilbao Stock Exchanges.
It has also explained that 5,592,778 million shares have been immobilized, which can not be transmitted in any way until the completion of the offer, from which it has specified that the price has been fixed by Federico Paternina, in accordance with the provisions of the current regulations.
New Tools for Car Experts
In these days of storms and accidents, not only car workshops win.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered a crash are towed to a workshop, where an expert must assess the damage suffered and what the cost of repair will be.
No loss is the same, and calculating parts costs and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
Calculating annually the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and workmanship, can take two or three hours.
Instead, with the support of the latest computer tools it would be a matter of minutes.
That’s why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Providers of services and solutions for claims assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information provided to them by manufacturers, then processing it and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the valuations are made with its products.
The other firms competing in the field of appraisal tools and information processing on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data supplied by manufacturers is far from straightforward.
According to Eduardo Vel<0xC3><0xA1>zquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with the information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, to the point that more versions, variants and drives have been released in the last five years than in the previous fifteen.
As soon as a new car hits the market, these companies get to work.
It is a very arduous task, because you have to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and enter its price.
In addition, a "smart" graphic image is made of each model where different parts of tourism can be "pricked".
If it is a mass-sale model, the job can be ready in a week if the process goes very fast.
If it is a minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has full information on 99.2% of the cars that are sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models they have information about Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile fleet that circulates, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the documentation work and the elaboration of the databases, Audatex has eight centers around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros annually in the development of these databases.
Every month 2.5 million data are included, and customers receive updates every other day.
The elaboration of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and offer various products.
The most frequent use focuses on repair and maintenance, but depending on which countries there are also tools for managing scrapping parts or to calculate the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that reports on the value of used in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support that professionals in the sector can provide.
This company offers ten different tools, being the star product AudaPlus, the standard solution for claims assessment, aimed at experts.
Includes cars, motorcycles and light or heavy commercial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting scales.
This tool is paid according to use, for each rating.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, a maximum of ten times a month.
Then each insurance company, which performs thousands of expert reviews, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it left the assembly line only by its chassis number.
AudaGlass focuses on the windows of vehicles, and AudaSubastas is a service open to the professional sector on the internet that allows bids for vehicles declared total loss.
Its statistics service is very useful to identify trends, perform geodemographic analyses or know the deviations by brands or models.
It can be studied, for example, how many models of a certain brand have passed through the workshop due to breakdowns or how many have suffered serious accidents in a given period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It markets, among others, Gt Estimate, which is also intended for experts and also provides digital images, access to parts or official prices and times of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa group founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of damage, breakdown or maintenance of the car.
The Gt Appraisals Guide is your historical benchmark product in the market.
They work with 24,000 users in workshops, 3,100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Their turnover has grown at a rate of 20% annually in the last three years, and in 2008 they invoiced 10.8 million euros.
At the beginning of last year they began their internationalization process, with the installation of an office in Paris.
Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and established in Spain in 1979.
According to company sources, 62% of its business is generated in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. They work with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
The global turnover of the Solera group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will reach 557 million dollars, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country the company will enter 19.1 million euros, 7.2% more than the previous year.
In 2005, the Solera group was worth $1 billion on the stock exchange, and now its shares are listed for a total value of $2.4 billion.
Since 2007 it has been listed on the New York Stock Exchange and is included in the Standard & Poor's benchmark index.
Internet Auction of Accidental Cars
Last October, the Solera group bought Autoonline, an online platform for the sale of cars such as motorcycles or special vehicles.
The transaction involved a disbursement of 59.5 million euros for 85% of the capital of the company, which could be extended next year to the remaining 15%.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of accessing an immense international market.
This valuation and sale service is exclusively aimed at professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, workshops, scrapyards and professional sellers who must register before starting operations.
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations throughout Europe, 500,000 of them in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website currently has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 experts.
3,000 ads are managed daily and about 100 new ads are included in the Spanish market every day.
Under Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been dropped cannot be recirculated, but certain parts that are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
Cars with historical value can be discharged even if they have been discharged after some strenuous efforts.
Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Workshop tool, the company Audatex guarantees that the user gets a budget in only four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the spare part, create a budget and generate a budget.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who to a greater or lesser extent are usually more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 cars, 109 off-roaders, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it you need a computer with an internet connection.
Once the model to be repaired is identified by its frame number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor price, surcharges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a catalog of references.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented system does not include estimated labor times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently the company Audatex is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with very good eyes, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inner face.
